    "body": "> Not entirely sure what this issue is about, but is this relevant when we rewrite in Rust? If not, we should close this\r\n\r\nmacOS uses `~/.bash_profile` for shell directives/etc. It does not use `~/.bashrc` which is the correct way and the way that foundryup does it. \r\n\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n\r\n# Only add foundryup if it isn't already in PATH.\r\nif [[ \":$PATH:\" != *\":${FOUNDRY_BIN_DIR}:\"* ]]; then\r\n  # if macOS use bash_profile\r\n\tif [[ $PLATFORM == 'darwin'* ]]; then\r\n\t\techo >>\"$HOME\"/.bash_profile && echo \"export PATH=\\\"\\$PATH:$FOUNDRY_BIN_DIR\\\"\" >>\"$HOME\"/.bash_profile\r\n\tfi\r\n# use bashrc everywhere else \r\n\t# Add the foundryup directory to the path and ensure the old PATH variables remain.\r\n\techo >>\"$PROFILE\" && echo \"export PATH=\\\"\\$PATH:$FOUNDRY_BIN_DIR\\\"\" >>\"$PROFILE\"\r\nfi\r\n```",
